TextEng: Greetings. Nice to see someone still alive out here. I'd prefer that we were talking somewhere safe, but it's still nice.
Text: 안녕하세요. 여기서 아직 살아있는 사람을 보니 반갑네요. 안전한 곳에서 얘기하면 더 좋겠지만, 그래도 반가워요.

TextEng: Other than legions of undead, a husband that puts his cart ahead of his family, and a plague that seems almost apocalyptic?
Text: 언데드 군단, 가족보다 수레를 더 챙기는 남편, 거의 세상 종말 같은 역병 말고요?

TextEng: Nope, nothing. really. I've been too busy trying to stay alive.
Text: 아뇨, 정말 아무것도요. 살아남느라 너무 바빴거든요.

TextEng: Good day to you.
Text: 좋은 하루 되세요.

TextEng: We'll be all right. Aldo will keep us safe. He's a good man. A bit too attached to the cart, I think, but a good man.
Text: 괜찮을 거예요. 알도가 우릴 지켜줄 거예요. 좋은 사람이에요. 수레에 좀 너무 집착하긴 하지만, 좋은 사람이에요.

TextEng: It's not such a nice wagon, dear.
Text: 그렇게 좋은 수레도 아니잖아, 여보.

TextEng: We can buy new things, dear.
Text: 새 물건은 사면 되잖아, 여보.

TextEng: Should we die for this lousy furniture? It was your mother's and smells funny.
Text: 이 허접한 가구 때문에 죽어야 해? 시어머니 거라 냄새도 이상한데.

TextEng: Travel, you said. Move to the big city, you said.
Text: 여행하자고 했잖아. 대도시로 이사하자고 했잖아.

TextEng: As... thoughtful... as your offer is, I think I'll stay with my husband. He can form sentences.
Text: 제안은... 사려 깊긴... 한데, 남편 곁에 있을게요. 그 사람은 문장은 만들 줄 아니까.

TextEng: You know, my old hound had that exact look on his face. All the time. Don't get me wrong, he was a SMART dog...
Text: 있잖아요, 우리 집 늙은 사냥개가 딱 저런 표정이었어요. 항상. 오해 마세요, 똑똑한 개였거든요...

TextEng: In answer to your masterfully constructed question, I have seen zombies, plague, and the madness of my husband. Danger enough?
Text: 훌륭하게 구성된 질문에 답하자면, 좀비, 역병, 그리고 미친 남편을 봤어요. 충분히 위험하죠?

TextEng: Good day. Take care. Read the occasional book.
Text: 좋은 하루 되세요. 조심하시고요. 가끔 책도 읽고.

TextEng: We've got to get to safety!
Text: 안전한 곳으로 가야 해!

TextEng: I blame the wagon. Not the plague, not zombies... the wagon.
Text: 다 수레 탓이야. 역병도, 좀비도 아니고... 수레.

TextEng: Well, my name is Mattily. As for why I am out here, that's a very good question. Why don't you ask the cart?
Text: 제 이름은 매틸리예요. 왜 여기 있냐고요, 아주 좋은 질문이네요. 수레한테 물어보시죠?

TextEng: I'm sorry for my stressed tone, but I'm growing tired of waiting for a wagon wheel in a zombie-infested street. You hear me, Aldo?!
Text: 짜증 섞인 말투는 죄송해요, 하지만 좀비 가득한 거리에서 수레바퀴 기다리는 것도 지치거든요. 들려요, 알도?!

TextEng: Save it, Aldo! I'm getting real tired of waiting for a wagon wheel in the middle of a zombie-infested street!
Text: 됐어, 알도! 좀비 가득한 거리 한복판에서 수레바퀴 기다리는 거 진짜 지쳤다고!

TextEng: I'm more concerned about finding Hector. Aldo sent him for wagon parts and I'm worried for his safety. Family friend, you understand.
Text: 헥터 찾는 게 더 걱정이에요. 알도가 수레 부품 구하러 보냈는데 안전이 걱정돼요. 가족 친구거든요, 아시죠.

TextEng: Oh, I'm sure we'll be fine. I see you have Hector with you. Now that he's here, we'll be all right. I was worried about him. Aldo! Look! It's Hector!
Text: 아, 이제 괜찮을 거예요. 헥터가 같이 있네요. 왔으니 이제 괜찮을 거예요. 걱정했거든요. 알도! 봐! 헥터야!

TextEng: Talk to Aldo, will you? He'll want to know Hector is safe.
Text: 알도한테 얘기해줄래요? 헥터가 무사하다는 거 알고 싶어할 거예요.

TextEng: Not nice enough to make up for my husband Aldo being dead and zombies crawling out of everywhere, but you know how it goes.
Text: 남편 알도가 죽고 좀비가 사방에서 기어 나오는 걸 상쇄할 만큼은 아니지만, 뭐 어쩌겠어요.

TextEng: Take your insults somewhere else. I've watched undead slaughter my husband - don't think I'll get scared of little old you. I don't need your help.
Text: 모욕은 다른 데 가서 하세요. 언데드가 남편을 죽이는 걸 봤어요 - 당신한테 겁먹을 것 같아요? 도움 필요 없어요.

TextEng: Well, since you've got Hector with you, there's less than nothing keeping me here. I mean, I'd hate to leave the beloved cart behind... so many conflicting emotions...
Text: 글쎄, 헥터가 같이 있으니, 여기 있을 이유가 전혀 없네요. 사랑하는 수레를 두고 가기 싫긴 한데... 복잡한 감정이...

TextEng: That was a joke. Thanks for the offer, but Hector and I can find our own way out from here. I appreciate your help, though. Do me a favor? Spit on the cart before you go. There's a good <boy/girl>.
Text: 농담이에요. 제안은 고맙지만, 헥터랑 저는 알아서 나갈게요. 도움은 고마워요. 부탁 하나 들어줄래요? 가기 전에 수레에 침 좀 뱉어주세요. 착한 <boy/girl>.

TextEng: As much as I'd like you to, my husband was waiting for Hector and... well, I'd like to know he's safe before I go running off. He's a family friend, and more important than the cart, if you ask me.
Text: 그러고 싶지만, 남편이 헥터를 기다리고 있었고... 뭐, 도망가기 전에 무사한지 알고 싶어요. 가족 친구고, 저한테 물으면 수레보다 중요하거든요.

TextEng: I see that. Well, he can look all he wants, he's not going to find him. Aldo died fighting for his beloved cart. The idiot.
Text: 알아요. 글쎄, 아무리 찾아봐도 못 찾을 거예요. 알도는 사랑하는 수레를 위해 싸우다 죽었어요. 바보같이.

TextEng: I am Mattily, and that cart is why I've waited here, and why my husband is dead. Frankly, I don't know why I'm here now. Zombies everywhere else, maybe.
Text: 저는 매틸리고, 저 수레 때문에 여기서 기다렸고, 남편이 죽었어요. 솔직히, 왜 아직 여기 있는지 모르겠어요. 다른 데는 좀비 투성이라서 그런가.

TextEng: Of course, if my husband would get us the heck out of here, it would be even nicer.
Text: 물론, 남편이 여기서 빨리 빼내줬으면 더 좋았겠지만.

TextEng: You know, thanks for the offer, but I think I'll make a run for it on my own. With Aldo gone, I don't see any point in staying. I was waiting for Hector... but he's probably dead.
Text: 있잖아요, 제안은 고맙지만, 혼자 도망갈게요. 알도가 없으니, 있을 이유가 없어요. 헥터를 기다렸는데... 아마 죽었겠죠.

TextEng: Thanks for the offer, but I'm going off on my own. People have been steering me wrong all night.
Text: 제안은 고맙지만, 혼자 갈게요. 밤새 사람들한테 잘못된 방향만 들었거든요.
